quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  11,63,"He said, “O my people, what do you think, if I should have clear proof from my Lord, and He has bestowed mercy upon me from Himself, who could protect me from Allah if I were to disobey Him? You would only increase me in loss."
  11,64,"O my people, this she-camel of Allah is a sign to you; so leave her to graze in Allah’s land, and do not touch her with harm, or else an imminent punishment will overtake you.”"
  11,65,"But they hamstrung her, so he said, “Enjoy yourselves in your homes for three days. That is an unfailing promise!”"
  11,66,"So when Our command came, We saved Sālih and those who believed with him, by Our mercy, and from the disgrace of that day. Your Lord is the All-Powerful, the All-Mighty."
  11,67,"The huge blast seized those who did wrong, and they fell dead in their homes,"
  11,68,"as though they had never lived there. Indeed, Thamūd denied their Lord; so away with Thamūd!"
  11,69,"Our messengers came to Abraham with glad tidings. They said, “Peace.” He said, “Peace.” And in a short while he brought a roasted calf."
  11,70,"When he saw their hands not reaching the food, he became suspicious and felt scared of them. They said, “Do not be scared. We have been sent to the people of Lot.”"
  11,71,"His wife was standing by and laughed after We gave her glad tidings of [the birth of] Isaac and Jacob after Isaac."